import LeanFX2.Tools.DependencyAudit

/-! # Tools/AuditAll — auto-generated per-decl axiom gates

Per-declaration `#assert_no_axioms` calls covering every kernel
theorem in the project.  Generated by `Tools/AuditGen.lean`.

## Structure

```lean
-- Layer 0 — Foundation
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Mode.Modality
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.RawTerm
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.RawTerm.rename
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.RawTermSubst.compose
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Ty
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Ty.subst
-- ... (all Layer 0 declarations)

-- Layer 1 — Term
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Term
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Term.rename
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Term.subst
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Term.subst0
-- ... (all Layer 1 declarations)

-- Layer 2 — Reduction
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Step
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Step.par
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.StepStar.mapStep
#assert_no_axioms LeanFX2.Conv
-- ... etc
```

## Generation

`Tools/AuditGen.lean` defines a tactic that crawls the namespace,
identifies every `theorem` / `def` / `inductive`, and emits a
`#assert_no_axioms` for each.  Run periodically; commit generated
output as this file.

## Why per-decl gates

Single global gate ("no axioms anywhere") is too coarse — debugging
is hard when one of 1000+ decls leaks.  Per-decl gates pinpoint the
violating decl immediately.

## Layered policy

Per `AXIOMS.md` and `CLAUDE.md` "Zero-axiom commitment — ABSOLUTE,
NO EXCEPTIONS":
* Every layer is strict zero-axiom.  No HoTT exception.  No
  Univalence carve-out.  No `@[univalence_postulate]` attribute.
* Univalence and funext enter the kernel via `Step.eqType` /
  `Step.eqArrow` reductions — they are real theorems with bodies
  `Conv.fromStep _`, NOT axioms.
* Gate fails if any axiom appears in any dependency tree, including
  the three Lean core axioms (`propext`, `Quot.sound`,
  `Classical.choice`).

## Dependencies

* `Tools/DependencyAudit.lean`

## Downstream

* CI build pipeline — auditAll is part of `lake build`

## Implementation plan (Layer 12)

1. Generate initial audit file from existing kernel decls
2. Wire into `lake build` (file is part of the library)
3. Re-generate on schedule (per-PR pre-commit hook?)

Target: ~600 lines (auto-generated; ~200 decl gates expected initially).
-/

